pageContext.claim: “I felt we were doing good but, you know, when [Republicans] haven't [won Michigan] in like 38 years or something [before 2016], you know, you could feel good, but you realize maybe it doesn't work out.”
pageContext.analysis: In 1988 — 28 years before the 2016 election —  George H. W. Bush won Michigan. He was the last Republican to do so before Trump.
